HEADWORD: Disassimilative
<hw>Dis`as*sim"i*la*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Having power to disassimilate; of the nature
of disassimilation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Disassimilative</qex> processes constitute a marked feature
in the life of animal cells.</q> <rj><qau>McKendrick.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

